<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TimeML><TIMEX3 tid="t0" functionInDocument="CREATION_TIME"/>The Japanese government will <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="FUTURE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">face</EVENT> a minimum 8.9  trillion yen (86 billion dollar) budgetary shortfall at the turn of the  <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE">century</TIMEX3> if the current tax structure is <EVENT eid="e2" class="STATE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">maintained</EVENT>, officials <EVENT eid="e3" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE">Tuesday</TIMEX3>.&#13;
A report <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PASTPART" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">submitted</EVENT> by the finance ministry to the tax council, an official  advisory panel which is <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE">now</TIMEX3> <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="PROGRESSIVE" polarity="POS" modality="none">working</EVENT> on reforming taxes, <EVENT eid="e6" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> the lack of funds  would <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">result</EVENT> from increasing social welfare costs.&#13;
Following the report, observers here <EVENT eid="e8" class="REPORTING" tense="PAST" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">said</EVENT> the council would likely  <EVENT eid="e9" class="I_ACTION" tense="NONE" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="would">recommend</EVENT> increases in indirect taxes when it <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE" tense="PRESENT" aspect="NONE" polarity="POS" modality="none">makes</EVENT> its own report in <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE">June</TIMEX3>.&#13;
